sql:
SELECT first_name, age, COUNT(*) OVER (PARTITION BY age) as age_group_count
FROM patients
WHERE age > 50;

SELECT test_name, result 
FROM blood_tests 
WHERE patient_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT patient_id) AS unique_patients_with_surgery
FROM surgeries
WHERE thyroid_surgery = 1;

external_knowledge:
- A goitre is an abnormal enlargement of the thyroid gland; 
- Thyroid tests, including TSH, T3, and TT4, are used to assess the function of the thyroid gland; 
- Lipid profile blood tests are used to measure the levels of different types of cholesterol and triglycerides in the blood; 
- These tests are often conducted to diagnose and monitor various health conditions, including thyroid disorders and cardiovascular disease.

